Paper: hep-th/9709197

Date: 1997-09-26

Title: The TBA, the Gross-Neveu Model, and Polyacetylene

Authors: Alan Chodos (Yale Univ.) and Hisakzau Minakata (Tokyo Metropolitan

Univ.)Comments: 9 pages (lamuphys) reference change

We summarize recent work showing how the Thermodynamic Bethe Ansatz may beused to study the finite-density first-order phase transition in theGross-Neveu model. The application to trans-polyacetylene is discussed, and thesignificance of the results is addressed.